  "prompt": "Why do I have red itchy balls all over my skin?",
  "response": "I\u2019m not a doctor, but there are several potential causes for red, itchy spots on the skin, and it's important to consult a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis. Some common causes might include:\n\n1. **Allergic Reactions**: You may be experiencing an allergic reaction to a substance such as soap, detergent, food, or medications.\n\n2. **Skin Conditions**: Conditions like eczema, psoriasis, or hives can cause red and itchy patches on the skin.\n\n3. **Infections**: Fungal infections, ringworm, or other skin infections may lead to red, itchy spots.\n\n4. **Insect Bites**: Bites from insects such as mosquitoes or fleas can cause localized itching and redness.\n\n5. **Heat Rash**: If you are in a hot and humid environment, sweat can become trapped in your skin, leading to a heat rash.\n\n6. **Contact Dermatitis**: This occurs when your skin comes in contact with an irritating substance or allergen.\n\n7. **Scabies**: This is caused by tiny mites burrowing into the skin and can lead to severe itching and a rash.\n\nIf you're experiencing persistent symptoms, it's best to see a healthcare provider to determine the underlying cause and get appropriate treatment.",
